Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.90,0:00:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Top Gear Car of the Year for 2000 is...{\i1}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.86,0:00:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Fiat Multipla.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.82,0:00:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And some of you still haven't forgiven us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.30,0:00:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But twelve months on, will the Multipla\N retain its controversial crown?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.38,0:00:50.86,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(15,30)}♪ "American Dream"\NJakatta
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.98,0:00:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You, the car buying British public,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.34,0:00:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,have a mind-boggling choice\N of more than 2000 different new cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.90,0:00:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, because\N we're here to reveal the best,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.74,0:00:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in our Top Gear Awards special.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.82,0:01:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is there is no\N such thing as a bad car anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.14,0:01:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means to win an award,\N excellence is a necessity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.06,0:01:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A car must be absolutely outstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.82,0:01:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There are five different categories,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.82,0:01:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's something for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.98,0:01:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what they say.\NLook after the pennies,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.62,0:01:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and the pounds will\N look after themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.86,0:01:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're determined to get\N the most medal for your money,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.82,0:01:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,then make our Best Value award\N part of your savings plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.46,0:01:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But, if your numbers do come up,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.78,0:01:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,then, rest assured, we will show you\N how to squander your lottery millions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.94,0:01:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with our Ultimate Dream Car.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.26,0:01:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll also be revealing the vehicle\N no 21st century family should be without,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.86,0:01:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,what the ideal mode of transport is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.50,0:01:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to make those endless shopping trips\N and the school runs more bearable,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.06,0:01:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the Best Family Car.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.66,0:01:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And for those precious weekends\N when you don't have to cart the kids around,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.66,0:01:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an award for the Best Driver's Car.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.30,0:01:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, the\Nmain announcement!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.66,0:02:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We will reveal the identity of the one car\N that does more things better than any other,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.30,0:02:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Top Gear's Car of the Year 2001.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.42,0:02:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Time then, for the first award!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.62,0:02:15.62,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(15.087,42.667)}♪ "Fools Gold"\NThe Stone Roses
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.02,0:02:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1)}London, the Square Mile,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.02,0:02:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1)}where the deals are done, and\N personal wealth is measured in millions.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.26,0:02:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the US economy is slowing,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.10,0:02:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and bonuses are set to be slashed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.78,0:02:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So city boys, like everyone else,\N will have to watch their spending.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.50,0:02:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(275,93.333)}But now, you've got an\N important lesson to learn,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.86,0:02:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(275,93.333)}Getting value for money doesn't\N necessarily mean buying cheap,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.46,0:02:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(275,70)}especially when it comes to cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.30,0:02:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In 2000, price cuts came from all quarters,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.14,0:02:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and with most manufacturers\Nhaving upped their specs,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.58,0:02:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}more and more cars find themselves\N eligible for the Best Value award.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.34,0:02:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Bargains last year came\N in all shapes and sizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.14,0:02:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which made choosing \NTop Gear's Best Value Car difficult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.22,0:02:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but not impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.50,0:02:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1)}Here are the runners-up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.70,0:02:57.03,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(15.975,38.667)}♪ "Sun Is Shining (De Luxe Edit)"\NFunkstar De Luxe
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.90,0:02:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Skodas are no longer\N laughing matters.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.06,0:03:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Octavia is practical,\N offers superb choice,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.18,0:03:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and were it not for\N the bulletproof build quality,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.38,0:03:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}you'd hear it groaning\Nunder the weight of extras.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.86,0:03:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Not bad for £ 9,800.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.26,0:03:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Korea, the country's got soul \Nbut the cars haven't.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.18,0:03:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, the Daewoo Tacuma\N could change all that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.58,0:03:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Starting at a bargain £ 12,500,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.74,0:03:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it offers the joy of Mini MPV ownership\Nat a fraction of the price of its rivals.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.26,0:03:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(275,90.667)}Also in the running was\N the Subaru Impreza WRX.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.90,0:03:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(275,90.667)}In a country where you need to\N remortgage before vegetable shopping,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.86,0:03:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(275,90.667)}the Japanese should\N be very proud of this.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.86,0:03:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\pos(275,90.667)}At £ 21,495, it's the most affordable\N performance car ever.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.54,0:03:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, those three\N came close, but no cigar.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.06,0:03:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The winner of the Top Gear\NBest Value Car award is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.74,0:03:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the SEAT León!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.14,0:03:49.74,Music,,0,0,0,,♪ "Brown Paper Bag (feat. Dynamite MC)"\NRoni Size / Reprazent
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.78,0:03:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,SEAT have emptied out \Nthe parts bin of parent Volkswagen,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.82,0:03:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and stuck together the best bits\N with more imagination and spark
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.82,0:03:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,than any modern day V-Dub\N could possibly hope for.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.94,0:04:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Buying under ten grand used to have all the glamour of a drug problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.82,0:04:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What little money you had it's gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.82,0:04:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody wants to know you anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.42,0:04:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and your best friend\Nbecomes the local dealer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.22,0:04:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the 1.4 S has changed all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.22,0:04:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Twin airbags, ABS, power steering,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.78,0:04:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and electric front windows,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.22,0:04:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(166.85,469.333)}mean you'd have to go\N a long way north of that price
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.34,0:04:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to get anything like the same package.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.02,0:04:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go for this, the entry-level 1.4 S,\Nyou're going to love its easygoing nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.42,0:04:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And those tightwad diesel fanatics\N who plump for the 1.9L TDI
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.18,0:04:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,are gonna stop pinching their pennies,\Nand start pinching themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.10,0:04:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But it's the drivers who go\N for the top-of-the-range Cupra,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.10,0:04:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}who will be laughing\N all the way to the bank,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.10,0:04:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and via the long route,\N if they've got any sense.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.66,0:04:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,At £14,995, it's a world cruise\Ncheaper than its close
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.34,0:04:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and more sluggish\N relation, the Golf GTI.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.06,0:04:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And, in comparison,\N it drives like a full blooded bull run.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.26,0:04:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, it's not up to Ford Focus\N levels of entertainment,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.98,0:05:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but brimming with pace\N and kit, it doesn't have to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.34,0:05:06.70,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(15.087,32)}♪ "Once Around The Block"\NBadly Drawn Boy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.06,0:05:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here's the thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.38,0:05:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,this is, actually, the quickest car you\N can buy for under 15 thousand quid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.90,0:05:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The turbo knocks out 180 BHP
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.70,0:05:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and it gets from nought\N to 60 in just 7.5 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.58,0:05:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,SEAT say "Enjoy yourself",
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.90,0:05:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and at this price,\N with this performance,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.70,0:05:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm on the verge of being \Nwhipped into a veritable frenzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.54,0:05:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.28,0:05:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The León range\N provides a brilliant alternative
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.65,0:05:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to cars with bloated\Nreputations and price tags,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.42,0:05:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you're a \Nbudget shopper or a boy racer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.46,0:05:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheap, cheerful and honest fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.38,0:05:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the SEAT León is\N Top Gear's Best Value Car for 2001.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.92,0:06:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(160.313,106.667)}Let's face it, scrimping and\N saving and worrying about
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.54,0:06:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the pound in your pocket\N can be absolute torture.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.46,0:06:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So do yourself a\Nfavour, stop saving
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.98,0:06:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and start dreaming.\NWho wants to be a millionaire
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.93,0:06:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when you can dream\Nof being a billionaire?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.50,0:06:26.70,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(16.862,32)}♪ "At The River"\NGroove Armada
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.56,0:06:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So, what will you choose \Nto get around your dream world?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.54,0:06:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Well, this isn't a bad start.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.86,0:06:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A 75 foot super yacht, ideal for\Ntaking you from A to B via the Bahamas.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.02,0:06:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The cost of this high life on the\Nocean waves? Well, the sky is the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.14,0:06:49.64,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(15.087,32)}♪ "Forever Texas"\NRobbie Williams
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.46,0:06:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Unless, of course, you've got\N one of these at your disposal.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.58,0:06:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A Sikorsky S-76,\Nthe Rolls-Royce of the skies.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.76,0:07:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In here it's like an\Nexecutive boardroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.98,0:07:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,only you're guaranteed\Nto go up in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.76,0:07:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So, with sea and air taken care of,\Nhow would you get about on land?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.28,0:07:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When it comes to choosing\N the fleet to fill your fantasy garage,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.06,0:07:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,only the most exclusive cars will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.70,0:07:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here are our suggestions, should\Nyou ever stumble across that blank check.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.60,0:07:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The first of our nominees\Nis the Ferrari 360 Spider.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.30,0:07:28.14,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(17.75,35)}♪ "The Force of Destiny: Overture"\NRoyal Philharmonic Orchestra
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.58,0:07:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The fastest way I\Nknow to top up your turn.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.90,0:07:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's ideal when the most important\Nthing in your life is simply to be seen.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.12,0:07:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for a Sunday\N outing with mum and dad,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.78,0:07:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what could be more perfect\Nthan a Bentley Arnage Red Label?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.90,0:07:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not so much giving them a lift,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.90,0:07:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as checking them into a very\N expensive hotel. And with 400 BHP,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.58,0:08:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you could take them\N to lunch at the Ritz in Paris
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.66,0:08:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and still be back\N home in time for tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.18,0:08:09.22,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(17.75,30)}♪ "Dancing In The Moonlight"\NToploader
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.72,0:08:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now, when the most important thing\N in your life is simply to be heard,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.42,0:08:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there's the TVR Speed 12.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.94,0:08:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Loud enough to bring\N down birds in light aircraft,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.62,0:08:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it's perfect for impressing\N your mates down the pub.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.44,0:08:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen right, my XR2\Nis putting out 200 BHP
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.94,0:08:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,at the front wheels,\N what's yours got?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,800.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.50,0:08:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.40,0:08:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But the vehicle with more\N global cachet than anything else,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.38,0:08:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and the winner of the Top Gear\N award for the Ultimate Dream Car is...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.26,0:08:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the £150,000 Lamborghini Diablo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.02,0:08:48.02,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(15.087,33.333)}♪ "Better Man"\NRobbie Williams
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.86,0:08:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Its roots lie in an\Nexotic era, but these
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.06,0:08:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,days its performance\Nlives mainly in fantasy land.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.14,0:09:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The 6-litre V12,\Naccording to the brochure,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.98,0:09:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,will do more than 205\Nmiles an hour, whilst
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.40,0:09:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,0-60 takes, well, just a couple\Nof turns of those 18 inches.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.18,0:09:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Even pootling in a\NDiablo is a real occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.12,0:09:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Your body sits deep\Nin the sculpted seats,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.52,0:09:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,your feet rest on\N the tiny race-like pedals,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.58,0:09:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and your hands wrap around\N a bull-embossed leather steering wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.22,0:09:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The gear change is a\Ndivinely muscular movement
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.54,0:09:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and the steering is\Nthe exact opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.23,0:09:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there is a\N Grand National being run back there,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.96,0:10:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,with every one of the 550\Nhorses wanting to win the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.23,0:10:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Believe me,\N this is naughtily noisy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.48,0:10:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All Diablos come\N with attitude as standard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.90,0:10:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sandwich one between a pair of Ferraris\N and the Lambo will be the most lusted after.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.06,0:10:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, they're just so exclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.06,0:10:23.98,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "Who Knows Where The Time Goes?"\NFairport Convention
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.24,0:10:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Not so long ago,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.62,0:10:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}200-mile-an-hour motors\N seemed to grow on trees,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.78,0:10:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but this monstrous mid-engine beast\N is one of the few remaining examples{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.26,0:10:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of a proud breed, the supercar.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.62,0:10:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's what makes it so special.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.08,0:10:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The stuff dreams are\Nmade of, you bet, and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.20,0:10:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,outrageous ones at that.\NThe Lamborghini Diablo
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.68,0:10:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,wins the Top Gear Award\Nfor the Ultimate Dream Car.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.82,0:11:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(275,86.667)}Of course the Lamborghini Diablo is a\N dream car, it costs more than a house.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.70,0:11:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(275,86.667)}But what about\N the people whose job it is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.46,0:11:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn everyday cars\Ninto something desirable?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.50,0:11:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the wheelers and\N dealers of dreams, the advertisers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.62,0:11:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Top Gear's\Naward for the best car ad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.56,0:11:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In fifth place, Audi,\N who've come over all trendy
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.22,0:11:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and employed a weight-border\N to help them advertise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.78,0:11:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, are they saying the Quattro's\N system is godlike and walks on water?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.50,0:11:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Or are they trying to say the A6\N handles like a big old barge?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.30,0:11:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Fourth place is taken by Fiat\Nwith their latest advert for the Punto,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.06,0:11:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which ably demonstrates\N what a good shopping car it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.70,0:11:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you live on the wrong\N side of Krakatoa, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.14,0:11:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. If you think\Nyou can do any better,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.94,0:11:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- You drive.\N- Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.62,0:12:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the mess\Nyou made to the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.38,0:12:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So after the drama of\Ncrashing waves and the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.58,0:12:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,magnificence of an\Nerupting volcano,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.00,0:12:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which bit of nature do\NVW use in their ads?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.54,0:12:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A muddy puddle \Nand a dirty dog. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.22,0:12:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Good ad, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.24,0:12:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- This one here, Dixon Road?\N- Dixon Road, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.70,0:12:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- Tenner will do it? \N- Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.74,0:12:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.42,0:12:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}BARLOW: Peugeot takes second place\Nthanks to magician David Blaine.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.24,0:12:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see the cards?\N'Cause I want you to try
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.71,0:12:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to think of one card from\Ninside, not this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.24,0:12:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,look closely, try to see\None. Did you see one?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.50,0:12:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It might have been\Ntoo fast, I'll do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.24,0:12:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to see one card\Nfrom inside, not that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.42,0:13:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say it, but you have\None, hold it in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.14,0:13:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I know this is not your card,\N this is not it, but I want you to visualize
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.24,0:13:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,your card right here, see it in\Nyour mind, see it right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.22,0:13:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}BARLOW: Now that\N is magic, Mr Daniels.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.29,0:13:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.24,0:13:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- The Peugeot 206 GTI.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.86,0:13:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- Magic, magic, magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.86,0:13:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- Now you see it,\N now you don't.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.19,0:13:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}BARLOW: But the winner\Nhad to be Land Rover,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.38,0:13:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}with the release of their\NFreelanders into the wild.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.26,0:13:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's an excellent ad that\Nworks on lots of levels.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.18,0:13:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It makes the car look good,\N it makes you think about the brand {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.50,0:14:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and best of all, it lets you\N brush up on your Swahili.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.18,0:14:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would have thought, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.58,0:14:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Here on the edge of the M25...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.98,0:14:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,stands the future,\N the Millenium House,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.34,0:14:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,designed to be the perfect\N family residence. How?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.34,0:14:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, according\Nto its architects,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.31,0:14:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it combines innovation,\Ntechnology and environmental
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.24,0:14:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness to make family\Nlife that bit more tolerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.99,0:14:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's a lawn on the roof,\Nwhich literally cleans the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.40,0:14:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The fridge uses less power than a\Nlight bulb. And there's a dual stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.86,0:14:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,extra powerful\Nprogrammable flush on the toilet,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.46,0:14:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for those occasions when...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,when... when you get...\N I think you get my drift.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.04,0:14:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the perfect family have their perfect\Nhouse, but what's their perfect car?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.34,0:15:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We first met the future in 1984,\N courtesy of the Renault Espace.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.78,0:15:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The latest version has\Ngreat engines and loads of space.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.26,0:15:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If you've been particularly\Ncarefree when it comes to{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.58,0:15:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}family planning,\Nthen it's ideal.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.58,0:15:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Otherwise, it's almost\Ntoo much of a good thing.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.90,0:15:03.87,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "I Wanna Be Like You"\NBig Bad Voodoo Daddy
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.90,0:15:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So try an Estate instead,\N and there's really{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.38,0:15:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}none better than the Volvo V70.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.94,0:15:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's got a boot so big\N it crosses time zones,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.86,0:15:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and it's packed\Nwith standard equipment.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.10,0:15:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In T5 form, you'll also be\Nthe coolest parents in the street,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.65,0:15:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but a very long Volvo is unlikely\Nto set next door's curtains twitching.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.62,0:15:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Whereas a Chrysler\NPT Cruiser will.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.90,0:15:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It'll turn your driveway\Ninto 50's America at a stroke,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.54,0:15:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and then you'll head off,\N not on a day trip,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.89,0:15:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but on a cruise instead.\NWhich will be fine,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.24,0:15:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}because this is the one American\Ncar that actually drives well.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.19,0:15:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite those crazy looks,\N it isn't quite versatile enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.46,0:16:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Our winner, though, and\NTop Gear's Best Family Car for 2001
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.62,0:16:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,most definitely is versatile enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.42,0:16:06.42,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "You See the Trouble With Me"\NBlack Legend
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.58,0:16:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, it's the Fiat Multipla.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.82,0:16:13.94,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "Groovejet (If This Ain't Love)"\NBlack Legend
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.10,0:16:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The car that turns as many\Nstomachs as it does heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.50,0:16:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, please stop groaning,\N this thing is quite brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.94,0:16:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's more,\NI'm going to prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.24,0:16:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We loved the funny Fiat\N when we first drove it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.34,0:16:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was new, but more\Nimportantly, it looked new.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.54,0:16:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We had no hesitation in making it\N our Family Car of the Year for 2000,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.46,0:16:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and despite it scaring the animals,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.62,0:16:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}we made it last year's overall\NCar of the Year as well.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.74,0:16:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes, it's that good.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.62,0:16:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is, why have\Nwe got such faith in this car?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.26,0:16:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, believe it or not, it isn't\Nreally all that weird or wacky.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.78,0:16:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's actually the most\Nsensible car available today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.82,0:16:52.82,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "I Get The Sweetest Feeling"\NJackie Wilson
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.30,0:16:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Let's look at the evidence.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.10,0:16:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Multipla proves\N that six into one does go.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.30,0:16:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And unlike other MPVs at full capacity,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.50,0:16:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there's still enough room\N left over for the weekly shop.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.34,0:17:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't cheat\Nby being as long as a Trin.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.10,0:17:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's noticeably\N shorter than a Ford Focus,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.02,0:17:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which means that you can wave goodbye\N to touch parking, if that's your bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.46,0:17:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, brace yourselves,\Nwe're going in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.30,0:17:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the interior of the Multipla\Nis even more difficult...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.78,0:17:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to get your head around than\Nthe exterior. We can't deny it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.82,0:17:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But crucially, it all works\N brilliantly. Primary colours,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.34,0:17:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,big, chunky, easy to use instruments
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.94,0:17:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and Ribena-friendly fabrics\Nmake for an atmosphere of fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.34,0:17:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's not so much\Na car, more of a cartoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.82,0:17:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,[cartoon sound effects]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.18,0:17:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ The closer you get ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.26,0:17:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ The better you look, baby ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.26,0:17:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ The better you look, \N the more I want you ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.22,0:18:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And as for those looks,\Nwell, let me tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.58,0:18:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,on the continent where\Nthey invented the word 'chic',
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.38,0:18:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,this ugly duckling has become\Nsomething of a fashion accessory.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.02,0:18:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The Fiat Multipla\Ndoesn't drive like a van,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.37,0:18:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't heave or wallow\Nthrough the corners,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.24,0:18:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and if your precious\Nlittle mites decide to use it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.30,0:18:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,as a jungle gym, it won't\N go weak at the knees.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.64,0:18:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've got a family, nothing\Nelse does the job quite so well,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.26,0:18:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,or with quite so much imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.86,0:18:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So there you go.\N Unequivocally, the Fiat Multipla{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.89,0:18:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is our Family Car of the Year for 2001.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.90,0:18:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What do you mean you're still\Nnot convinced? Well, it's your loss.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.30,0:18:51.30,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "Novio"\NMoby
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.30,0:18:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}NEDDELL: Time for\Nthe penultimate award,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.42,0:18:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the Best Driver's Car.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.26,0:18:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Exquisite handling isn't enough,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.06,0:18:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the winner needs to be equally\N at home crossing continents{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.86,0:18:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}as scorching round circuits.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.22,0:19:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(275,65)}But we've imposed a £50,000 price limit,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.42,0:19:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(275,85)}so you can forget all your\N supercars, like this Porsche 911.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.14,0:19:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yet the shortlist is still\Npretty mouthwatering{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.98,0:19:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and our contenders come\Nin all shapes and sizes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.88,0:19:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's a hatchback, a saloon,\Na sports car and a coupe.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.86,0:19:17.86,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "Local Boy In The Photograph"\NStereophonics
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.24,0:19:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The judging isn't going to\Nbe easy, but it will be fun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.24,0:19:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowadays, hot hatches are\Nmost people's introduction
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.30,0:19:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to high performance motoring.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.26,0:20:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And this Renault Sport Clio 172\Nis a very serious proposition indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.38,0:20:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only has it beat\Nevery other hot hatch around,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.02,0:20:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,its performance embarrasses so much\Nmore expensive machinery as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.30,0:20:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,With its nimble handling\Nand racy interior,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.22,0:20:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a very tempting choice.\NBut once you've tasted
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.34,0:20:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the sensitive feel of a good rear\Nwheel drive, you know it just can't win.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.34,0:20:23.64,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "Sing It Back"\NMoloko
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.24,0:20:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So what about this four wheel\N drive Mitsubishi Evo 6,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.02,0:20:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}forged in the World Rally Championship\Nto cope with everything{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.98,0:20:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}from frozen Finnish lakes\Nto dusty African deserts?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.50,0:20:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's outrageous rubber\Nripping fun on an open racetrack,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.78,0:20:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but its frantic\Nturbocharged power deliver
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.74,0:20:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and ever varying degrees\Nof both understeer and oversteer
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.42,0:20:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,make it manic\Nrather than magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.70,0:20:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So how about the TVR Tuscan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.94,0:21:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,380 homemade horsepower,\Nsuperb good looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.94,0:21:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of nice quirky little\Ntouches everywhere you look.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.06,0:21:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, a best-of-both-worlds\Nremovable hard top
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.74,0:21:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the most stylish interior\Non the market today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.82,0:21:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,British through and through,\NI'd love it to be our winner,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.54,0:21:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's just a little bit\Ntoo much of a bulldog
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.47,0:21:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for that rewarding yet\Nrestful drive we're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.22,0:21:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Which brings us to last year's\NBest Driver's Car, the BMW M Coupe.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.22,0:21:28.22,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "Sunset (Bird of Prey)"\NFatboy Slim
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.30,0:21:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It still provides the most relaxed\N on the edge motoring available today,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.10,0:21:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}complete with a silken\Nstraight-six power plant{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.90,0:21:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and undeniably eye-catching looks.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.66,0:21:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And it definitely would have been\Nour winner if we hadn't discovered this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.86,0:22:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The Noble M12.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.86,0:22:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,On the outside it has\Nthe looks of a supercar.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.54,0:22:14.94,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "Finished Symphony"\NHybrid
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.42,0:22:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the inside it feels like a supercar,\Nwith this strikingly sculptured dash
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.18,0:22:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,threatening warp speed\Nbefore you even move.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.24,0:22:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one thing, though,\Nthat's not like a supercar. It's price tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.46,0:22:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,At just under £45,000, it's half\Nthat of a Ferrari 360 or 911 Turbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.14,0:22:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The brainchild of one man\Nand his shed, Lee Noble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.90,0:22:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is a rare example of a British\Nsports car dream come true.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.22,0:22:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Production's now underway{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.66,0:22:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and first deliveries\Nare due in the summer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.24,0:23:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's powered by a 2.5 litre Ford V6\N which doesn't sound that special,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.50,0:23:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but twin turbos, 310 horsepower,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.98,0:23:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and 60 in a nats over four seconds does.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.86,0:23:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Those turbos progressively boost the power
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.06,0:23:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,while their whooshing\Nand wheezing really get you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.26,0:23:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in the mood for the best bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.98,0:23:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The handling.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.24,0:23:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The steering is one of the best\N I've ever experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.62,0:23:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can consistently\Nput the front wheels...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.18,0:23:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly where you want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.22,0:23:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do turn into a corner a bit too\Nquickly, the rear of the car will slide out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.74,0:23:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But it all happens with so much\Nfeel that even an eight year old
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.78,0:23:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,would naturally correct it and\Npower slide out of the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.50,0:24:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The M12 is as equally at home\Ngoing for a long distance cruise
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.34,0:24:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is attacking a race track.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.70,0:24:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It may only be a two-seater,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.14,0:24:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's plenty of tailored luggage\Nspace so touring is no problem at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.74,0:24:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,\NMonte Carlo, here we come.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.70,0:24:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Noble M12 GT is Top Gear's\NBest Driver's Car for 2001.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.70,0:24:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, to the announcement of\NTop Gear's Car of the Year for 2001.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.34,0:24:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it's nothing that you have seen\N in the last 30 minutes, because
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.91,0:24:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,excelling in a single category\Njust isn't quite enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.02,0:24:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Top Gear's Car of the Year\Nhas to be a consummate all-rounder.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.94,0:24:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But before we reveal the winner,\Nhave a look at what it had to beat.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.24,0:24:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Cars like the dinky Audi A2.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.38,0:25:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as much of a trinket\Nas it is a town car.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.34,0:25:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It is extremely economical, and\Nit was built by robots who actually care.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.89,0:25:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But, as our Car of the Year proves,\Nyou don't have to buy German{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.70,0:25:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to guarantee good build quality.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.34,0:25:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}NEEDELL: Our next runner up,\N the BMW X5, defies the laws of physics.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.62,0:25:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the first 4x4 that handles\Nlike a car and a sports car at that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.38,0:25:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But prices start at £33,000\Nand that's a bit on the steep side.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.16,0:25:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Whereas our overall winner is a\Ntouch more attainable from £14,595.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.64,0:25:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the Honda Civic isn't really fun,\Nnor is it particularly good looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.42,0:25:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just so clever, so sensible,\Nso reliable and so versatile.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.18,0:25:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind you, all of those things apply\Nto our Car of the Year as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.24,0:25:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For 99% of the time, our winner would do\Nabsolutely everything you asked of it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.86,0:26:03.36,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "Don't Tell Me"\NMadonna
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.70,0:26:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}BUTLER-HENDERSON: The new\nSubaru Impreza could have{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.06,0:26:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}been a car of the year,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.34,0:26:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}if its looks hadn't divided opinion.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.62,0:26:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You either hate\Nthem or despise them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.78,0:26:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But believe me, four door saloons\Nhave never been so much fun.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.30,0:26:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Which is pretty true\Nfor our Car of the Year.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.70,0:26:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's no rally machine but nevertheless\Noffers a lively, entertaining drive.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.22,0:26:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When it comes to the environment,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.82,0:26:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,motor manufacturers\Nhave a conscience too.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.38,0:26:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Particularly those\Nbrainy boffins at Toyota.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.10,0:26:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This Prius is a four-seater saloon,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.14,0:26:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,which combines\N a super clean electric motor
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.62,0:26:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with a very fuel-efficient petrol one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.77,0:26:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all very clever but perhaps\Nmore a car for next year than this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.46,0:26:47.96,Music,,0,0,0,,{\pos(20,35)}♪ "Saltwater"\NChicane
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.82,0:26:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,NEEDELL: {\i1}So, what is the\NTop Gear Car of the Year for 2001?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.02,0:26:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,BUTLER-HENDERSON:{\i1} It's something\nthat combines the best qualities{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.41,0:26:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}of the other nominees\Nin just one package.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.74,0:26:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}BARLOW: It's all things to all men.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.94,0:27:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the Ford Mondeo.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.78,0:27:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What appeals to me\Nis the way it drives.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.54,0:27:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This Mondeo hasn't been\Nengineered by faceless accountants,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.34,0:27:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but by enthusiasts, making\Nthose everyday journeys
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.42,0:27:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that bit more fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.22,0:27:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But, perhaps most significantly\Nis what this means for Ford.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.82,0:27:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Along with the Puma and the Focus,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.86,0:27:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,this is their third Top Gear\NCar of the Year award.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.66,0:27:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody, somewhere is\Nmaking the right decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.86,0:27:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But the fight back\Nhas already begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.18,0:27:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Renault, Citroën and Volkswagen\Nare all gunning for the Mondeo.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.50,0:27:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Find out how they get on when the new\Nseries of Top Gear starts on February 22nd.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.86,0:27:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,For now though, we'll let the\NMondeo have its moment of glory.
